casebody.data:
Fitzgerald, Appellant, v. Fach, Respondent. (Superior Court of New York City, General Term. January 6, 1890.) Appeal from jury term. Action by Garret Fitzgerald as administrator against Charles Fach.

Argued before Sedgwick, C. J., and Freedman and Ingraham, JJ.

George C. Coffin, for appellant. Thomas F. Grady and Theodore Connoly, for respondent. Per Curiam.

Judgment and order affirmed, with costs.
